Q_DESC:
Two integers A and B are the inputs. Write a program to find GCD and LCM of A and B. 

Mandatory:

1. Create a new class and a method named "great" that takes two arguments of type integer. The method type is integer
public int great(int gcd,int lcm)

a .Method Name = great
b. Argument = Two Arguments with type integer and variable name as "gcd" and "lcm"
c. Access specifier = public
d. Method return type = integer

2. Create an instance in the main method as "objname" and access the "great" method
